  "text": "For the latter, [CITATION_1] proposes a nuclear norm minimization over multi-fold Hankel matrices approach, [CITATION_2] develops a reweighted trace minimization (RWTM) plus matrix pencil and (auto-)pairing (MaPP) method, where RWTM fully exploits the multilevel Toeplitz (MLT) structure and utilizes the sparsity to obtain the covariance estimates, and MaPP calculates the Vandermonde decomposition. As [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] involve solving a semidefinite programming (SDP), their computation complexities are very high.",
